message_1: What is the time complexity of sorting an array of 100,000 integers using selection sort algorithm?
message_2: The time complexity of the selection sort algorithm is O(n^2), where n is the number of elements in the array. In this case, n = 100,000. Therefore, the time complexity of sorting an array of 100,000 integers using the selection sort algorithm is O(100,000^2) or O(10^10).
